2Q25 Review: Fen Wing Lao jiao and Yanghe

Sellthrough hiccups due to anti- extraigance policies since May increased channel pressure, despite 2Q off- season. Some channel checks indicated marginal mitigation in Aug. Next key monitor is Mid- Autumn/National Days peak season. We still expect lingering impacts on demand despite a lower base in 2H. The sector has been at the bottom and policies accelerated the destocking cycle, while we are still waiting for demand to turnaround.

Fen Wine: 2Q revenue was flat and NP declined by \(13.5\%\) yoy to RMB7.44bn/1.86bn. Fen Wine remained flat while other products was down \(3.5\%\) yoy. By market, Shanxi/ outside Shanxi sales were \(- 5\% +4\%\) yoy. Gpm declined by 3.2ppts, which we think is mainly due to unfavorable product mix shift with higher- end products sellthrough impacted more. SG&A ratio increased 2.8ppts mainly due to higher sales tax ratio, while selling expense ratio was flat yoy.

Maintain Hold with new PT RMB233. We trim our earnings forecasts by \(10 - 12\%\) in 25- 27E on higher- than- expected industry pressure under anti- extravagance policies. Our new PT was RMB233 (vs. previous RMB234) as we raise our mid- term growth assumptions considering follow- up recovery in later years. Maintain Buy.

Laojiao: 2Q revenue/NP decreased by \(8\% /11\%\) yoy to RMB7.1bn/3.1bn, relatively better than market estimates considering consumer demand headwinds (esp in high end), and competition. 1H mid- to- high- end baijiu was down \(1.1\%\) with vol \(+13.3\%\) ASP down \(12.7\%\) . Gpm was down 1ppt, due to unfavorable mix shift. SG&A expense ratio was up 2.4ppts, due to 3.7ppts higher sales tax ratio, despite 1.2ppt savings in selling expense ratio. Contract liabilities increased by RMB1.2bn yoy to RMB3.53bn at the end of 1H25.

Maintain Hold with new PT RMB140.8. We trim our earnings forecasts by \(2 - 9\%\) in 25- 27E on near- term industry pressure under anti- extravagance policies and lower interest income. Our EBIT forecasts was changed by \(- 9 / - 6 / 0\%\) in 25/26/27E, with improved expense control. For 2H25, the co intends to 1) enhance channel cultivation and penetration to markets below county- level; 2) product innovation, incl. 28- degree Guojiao 1573, etc. 3) Solidify base category, while also focus more on mid- high- end mass mainstream products, ie. bottled baijiu products. 4) Further improve digital marketing and expense investment efficiency.

Yanghe: 2Q revenue/NP decreased by \(43.7\% /62.7\%\) yoy to RMB3.7bn/707m. By product, mid- high end/ low- end baijiu declined by \(36.5\% /26.4\%\) yoy in 1H25. By region, 1H25 sales inside/ outside Jiangsu stopped by \(26\% /43\%\) , respectively. Gpm was down 0.4ppt while SG&A ratio was up 12.3ppts, coming from 6ppt up in sales tax, and 2.3/4ppts up in selling expense/G&A expense ratio

Maintain Hold with new PT RMB69.6. We trim our earnings forecasts by \(6 - 26\%\) in 25- 27E to factor in near- term industry pressure under anti- extravagance policies and more intense industry competition. Mr. ZHANG Liandong resigned in early Jul and Mr. GU Yu has been elected as the new chairman since 21 Jul. The upgraded 7th Sea Blue was launched in late Mar, still priced at RMB100 range, and was put forwarded to Jiangsu market ending- 2Q. We think markets outside Jiangsu still need longer time to deleverage for this new product, and it will pay more attention to solidify base markets first under weak industry demand.

Fen Wine's strengths are its strong branding and distinctive flavour. It is the representative brand of Qing Xiang baijiu, which has a long history. Reforms since 2017 have given the company a clearer market strategy, better operating efficiency, more streamlined product portfolio, and stronger distribution channel. Future growth to be driven by both nationwide expansion and product mix upgrades.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

Macro environment is stable. Consumers continue to trade up to more premium products from mid- to low- end products. Sales CAGR of \(3\%\) in 2024- 2027E, with gross margin stable and mild decline in SG&A expense ratio. DCF- based PT of RMB233.

Macroeconomic growth is better than expected. Consumption upgrade accelerates with rising individual disposable income. Sales CAGR accelerates with faster nationwide expansion and product mix upgrade. DCF- based PT of RMB270.
Macroeconomic growth slows down significantly. Consumers' income growth decelerates, and they trade down to cheaper liquor. Sales CAGR decelerates with product mix downgrade. DCF- based PT of RMB135.

Top Material Issue(s): 1) Food safety and product quality are most important. Fen Wine has over 1.1mn mu (Chinese unit of \(\sim 666.7\) sq.m) of raw grain planting bases to ensure healthy, green raw materials, and it executes strict quality control through production. 2) Environmental protection is a key issue for baijiu manufacturers as water is a major resource and impacts the ecosystem around their factories. Natural gas, water, slag, green environment, carbon, etc, all matter.

Company Target(s): 1) To ensure green, low carbon development, follow national goals of peak carbon emissions in 2030 and carbon neutrality in 2060, ensure production technology and production zone allocate water resources effectively. 2) To enhance production quality control, improve eco- industrial chain, target to build a "organic, green, ecological, recyclable" industrial demonstration project of China baijiu industry.

Qs to Mgmt: 1) How to balance ecological conservation with capacity expansion? 2) How much environmental protection cost is expected in medium- to- long term? Any plans to set a medium- to long- term timeline for environmental mgmt.?

Earnings release Sales growth of Qinghua 30 Fuxing version Ex- factory price hike Macro economic stimulus Better than expected channel inventory depletion & improved sell- through or distributors' confidence

We see sell- through headwinds and intensified competition for high- end bajiu. We are positive on LaoJiao's strategy to focus on core product Cellar 1573 (premium) and base markets (Southwest and North China, etc) and its digitalization investments to track sell- through, but we expect revenue growth slowdown to mitigate channel inventory pressure in near term.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

Base Case, CNY140.8,+3%  - Macro environment is stable. Demand for premium liquor keeps growing with steady consumer sentiment. Consumers trade up to premium liquor.  - Not much change in Cellar 1573 retail price gap with Wuliangye. Distribution network continues to expand into South, Central, and East China.  - Maintain market position in base markets  - Price target of RMB140.8 based on DCF.

Upside Scenario, CNY182,+33%  - Macroeconomic growth is better than expectations. Helped by stronger consumer sentiment, premium liquor demand growth accelerates. Increasing number of consumers trade up to premium liquor.  - Cellar 1573 sees strong demand, and its retail price increases close to Wuliangye level.  - Development of mid- range and low- end products better than expectations.  - Price target of RMB182 based on DCF.

Downside Scenario, CNY86,- 37%  - Macroeconomic growth slows down significantly. Consumers' income growth decelerates, and they trade down to cheaper liquor.  - Competition intensifies and demand for Cellar 1573 deteriorates.  - Channel destocking, distributors suspend contracts with LaoJiao.  - Price target of RMB86 based on DCF.

Top Material Issue(s): 1) Food safety and product quality are most important. The company is committed to producing high- quality baijiu, advocating a healthy lifestyle, built and improved the six- factor mgmt. system (incl. organic, quality, safety, environment, measurement and energy). 2) Environment protection is also a key issue for baijiu manufacturers as they use water as a major resource and impact the ecosystem around their factories. Natural gas, water, slag, green environment, carbon and other ecological factors all matter. 3) Corruption is an issue that high- end baijiu companies need to face.

Company Target(s): 1) Reduce carbon- dioxide emissions through innovative electricity consumption models, electricity alternative trading programs, purchase of green electricity, etc. 2) Continue to develop green brewing technology to promote the development of the Chinese baijiu industry towards energy- saving and recycling.

Qs to Mgmt: 1) How do you balance ecological conservation with capacity expansion plans? 2) Any plans to set a medium- to long- term timeline for environment management issues? What are the obstacles?
Catalysts  - Price hike  - Recovery in sales of low- end products  - Macro economic stimulus  - Better than expected channel inventory depletion & improved sell- through or distributors' confidence

Yanghe has a strong track record of aggressively revamping its product portfolio to seek better growth. However, its earnings may face shortterm pressure after the overhaul. We thus need to monitor Yanghe's pipeline. Domestic market (Jiangsu) faces competition from King's Luck with solid channel building, and consumers in Jiangsu province are shifting their interests amid market competition. Markets outside Jiangsu face inventory challenges.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

Largely smooth transition during new product launches. Yanghe defends its market share in Jiangsu province while stabilizing its market share outside Jiangsu. Channel inventory is gradually depleted. DCF- based price target of RMB70.5.

Very smooth product transition: distributors stock up on new products without needing to destock old products. Gains market share in both Jiangsu and outside Jiangsu. Greater gross margin expansion. Faster than expected inventory depletion, successful launch of new products DCF- based price target of RMB94.2.

Difficult product transition, with distributors reluctant to procure new products due to excessive inventory of old products. Loses share in Jiangsu province (likely due to targeted strategies from King's Luck). Expense ratio increases due to more intense market competition. DCF- based price target of RMB44.8.

Top Material Issue(s): 1) Food safety and product quality are the most important for F&B manufacturers. The company established a food safety control system across its entire industry chain, and achieved one- stop traceability from raw materials to finished products through MES, LIMS, supplier cooperation management platforms, etc. 2) Environment protection is also a key issue for bajjiu manufacturers as they use water as a major resource and impact the ecosystem around their factories. Natural gas, water, slag, green environment, carbon and other ecological factors all matter.
Company Target(s): 1) Actively build a green development system featuring energy conservation, emission reduction, and low- carbon development. 2) Comply with CASS- CSR4.0 and SDGs.

Qs to Mgmt: 1) How do you balance ecological conservation with capacity expansion plans? 2) Do you have any plans to set a medium- to long- term timeline for environment management issues? What are the obstacles?
Price hikes Sales updates on product upgrades. Marco economic stimulus. Better than expected channel inventory depletion & improved sell- through or distributors' confidence

Luzhou Laojiao is a large liquor manufacturer in China, with its history dating back to the Qin or Han Dynasty. Headquartered in southern Sichuan, the company is the origin of China's strong aromatic liquor, and its brewing technique is a 23- generation inheritance. The company has two major brands: National Cellar 1573 and Luzhou Laojiao. The company listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange in 1994.

Jiangsu Yanghe is a national large- scale liquor manufacturer in China. The company owns two Chinese time- honored brands with over 1,300 years of history, namely Yanghe and Shuanggou, and six Chinese well- known trademarks. The company created mellow liquor in 2002, which is a new type under China's strong aromatic liquor but with a mild taste. It launched the Yanghe Spirit Classic series in 2003, which has become a leading mellow liquor brand in China. The company was listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange in 2009.

Fen Wine was established in 1948 in Shanxi province. It is a representative manufacturer of Qing Xiang baijiu in China. The company has three key brands: Fen, mainly for mid- to high- end liquor; Xing Hua Cun, for low- end liquor; and Chu Yeh Ching, for healthcare liquor. It was listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange in 1994.

We value Luzhou Laojiao based on a fundamental DCF approach (CoE \(9.5\%\) , TG \(2\%\) ). Risks to downside: intensified market competition; unexpected channel de- stocking; macro slowdown; potential consumption tax reform; food safety issues as well as failure to ramp up mid- end and low- end products.

We value Jiangsu Yanghe based on a fundamental DCF approach, factoring in \(9.5\%\) WACC and \(1\%\) TG. Upside risks: better- than- expected nationwide expansion with product upgrade version and easing down market competition. Downside risks: intensified market competition; macro slowdown; potential consumption tax reform; and food safety issues.

We use a DCF approach to value the company, factoring in \(3.9\%\) risk- free rate, \(5.6\%\) equity premium, \(1.0x\) beta, \(0\%\) target D/DE, a terminal growth rate of \(2\%\) , in line with other baijiu companies under our coverage. Key downside risks: more severe pandemic impact; intensified market competition; consumption tax reform; food safety issues.
